{"label":"React JS - Intro","id":"reactjs","list":[{"label":"Multiple Choice Question","type":"mcq","id":"test","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Question","allowFrac":false},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"What is React primarily used for?","options":"Building user interfaces\nManaging databases\nCreating servers\nHandling operating systems"},{"qText":"React was developed by which company?","options":"Meta\nGoogle\nMicrosoft\nTwitter"},{"qText":"What is the command to create a new React app using Create React App?","options":"npx create-react-app myApp\nnpm build react myApp\nreact new myApp\nnpm start react myApp"},{"qText":"React components must return _____.","options":"A single root element\nMultiple root elements\nA database connection\nAn object"},{"qText":"JSX stands for _____.","options":"JavaScript XML\nJava Syntax Extension\nJavaScript Extension\nJava eXpression"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"In React, data is passed from parent to child using _____.","options":"Props\nState\nReducers\nEvents"},{"qText":"Which hook is used for managing component state in functional components?","options":"useState\nuseEffect\nuseReducer\nuseContext"},{"qText":"Which hook is commonly used to perform side effects like API calls?","options":"useEffect\nuseState\nuseMemo\nuseRef"},{"qText":"What is the default port for running a React app using Create React App?","options":"3000\n8080\n5000\n4000"},{"qText":"In React, keys are used to _____.","options":"Identify elements in a list\nStyle components\nPass data as props\nDefine component types"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which of the following is a correct way to write a React functional component?","options":"function MyComponent() { return <h1>Hello</h1>; }\nclass MyComponent extends React.Component {}\nReact.createComponent(\"MyComponent\")\nconst MyComponent = React.Component()"},{"qText":"React follows which architecture?","options":"Component-based architecture\nMVC architecture\nMVVM architecture\nLayered architecture"},{"qText":"What is the purpose of useContext hook?","options":"To consume context values in components\nTo manage local state\nTo fetch API data\nTo memoize values"},{"qText":"Which method is used to render React elements to the DOM in React 18+?","options":"createRoot().render()\nReactDOM.render()\nReactMount.render()\nDOM.render()"},{"qText":"What is the purpose of React Router?","options":"Navigation between different views/pages\nManaging component state\nHandling async requests\nImproving performance"}]}]},{"label":"Drag and Drop","id":"dragdrop","type":"matchByDragDrop","data":{"fontSize":"1.3rem","dashWidth":80,"text":"Function or class that returns UI elements - *component* \nUsed to pass data from parent to child component - *props * \nA special object to store and manage local data inside a component - *state* \nReact hook for adding side effects (like API calls, timers) - *useEffect* \nJavaScript XML syntax extension used to write UI in React - *JSX* \nRepresents UI in memory and updates efficiently without reloading the whole DOM - *virtual DOM* \nReact hook to declare and update state variables - *useState* \nRenders React components into the actual DOM  - *ReactDOM.render()*"}},{"type":"classifySentence","label":"True or False","id":"true-false","data":{"title":"True or False","types":[{"name":"True","text":"React is a JavaScript library used for building user interfaces.\n            JSX allows writing HTML-like syntax inside JavaScript.\n            Functional components in React can use hooks to manage state.\n            The useEffect hook can be used to perform side effects such as fetching data.\n            React components must return exactly one root element.\n            Keys in React lists should always be unique to avoid rendering issues.\n            React Router is used to manage navigation between different pages or views in a React application."},{"name":"False","text":"React was developed by Google.\n            In React, data flows from child to parent by default.\n            ReactDOM.render() is still the standard method for rendering components in React 18+."}]}},{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks","fontSize":"1.4rem","text":"React was developed by *Meta (Google, Microsoft) *.\n        The syntax extension used in React to write HTML inside JavaScript is called *JSX (JSDoc, XJS )*.\n        In React, data is passed from parent to child components using * Props (State, Context)*.\n        The hook used to manage state in functional components is *useState(useEffect, useReducer)*.\n        To perform side effects like API calls in functional components, we use the *useEffect(useMemo, useRef)* hook.\n        React applications created with Create React App usually run on port *3000 (8080,5000)* .\n        A unique *key(id, name)* should be given to elements in a list to help React identify them."}}]}